CNCP v1 22692
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6509: async clientPrefetch hook - analog of serverPrefetch, waiting for data loaded on client",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:43.015380+00:00",
  "text": "async clientPrefetch hook - analog of serverPrefetch, waiting for data loaded on client\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\n\r\nHere are discussions: https://github.com/vuejs/vue-router/issues/1144 https://github.com/vuejs/vue/issues/7209 https://github.com/vuejs/pinia/discussions/988\r\nThere are cases where you need some data fetched before other components are initialized (mount hook called), for example authentication checked or user data fetched.\r\nCurrently need to use watches, which might be multiple, instead of a simple mounted hook in child components.\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\n\r\nJust the same as serverPrefetch, but on client.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
